news.title: Asian Granito India posts net profit of Rs 54 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Asian Granito India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 414.57 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 20 per cent from Rs 344.72 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ansal Properties & Infrastructure posts net loss of Rs 29 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Ansal Properties & Infrastructure's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 146.10 crore in Q2 FY22, a dip of 37 per cent from Rs 231.41 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: China's Yango Group, investors agree to extend dollar bond maturities: Source
news.para: Due to technical reasons, the company is still soliciting bondholders' approval for a payment extension on a February 2023 dollar bond putable on Friday, but the bond is not considered to be in default, the source said.

news.title: UK's Landsec sells London office property to Blackstone for $263 million
news.para: Harbour Exchange, located in the Docklands area, comprises two redeveloped office buildings, housing datacentre and office space, and was let to Equinix (UK) Ltd with an unexpired lease term of nearly 20 years.

news.title: Explained: China's Kaisa Group and the chairman behind it
news.para: Kaisa has more than $59 million in interest payments due on Thursday and Friday, with 30-day grace periods for both. Kaisa has the most offshore bonds - $10.9 billion at the end of June - of any Chinese developer after Evergrande.

news.title: NBCC fined Rs 5 lakh for violating dust control norms in East Delhi
news.para: "We conducted an inspection of the NBCC project in Karkardooma and found that it has not taken dust control measures at some places. Accordingly, a fine of Rs 5 lakh has been imposed on the company," Gopal Rai said.

news.title: Enforcement directorate detains IREO's managing director
news.para: ​Lalit Goyal was stopped by immigration authorities on Thursday at the Indira Gandhi International (IGI) airport here on the basis of an ED look out circular.

news.title: Builder-buyer talks from Nov 15 in Greater Noida to resolve disputes
news.para: On November 15, the meeting would be held between stakeholders of Gaur Son's Gaur City 2's 16 Avenue, then Panchtatva Promoters' Galaxy Wega on November 18, according to the schedule.

news.title: After Covid lull, societies in Ahmedabad put redevelopment on fast track
news.para: Around 105 societies, mainly low-rises in posh western areas, have either agreed or are in the midst of signing MoUs with developers to raze and rebuild their houses. Of these, 55 societies gave their consent in 2021.

news.title: Gurugram: 25 illegal shops built in DLF areas razed
news.para: The two sectors fall under the DLF area located close to Sarhaul border of Delhi and Gurgaon. The market value of land in this area is around Rs 2 lakh to Rs 2.5 lakh per square yard.

news.title: Omaxe posts net loss of Rs 42 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Omaxe's net consolidated total income stood at Rs Rs 191.34 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 17 per cent from Rs 163.47 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body receives lowest bid to mechanically run C&D waste plant
news.para: Two companies had participated in the bid to run the C&D waste plant mechanically, out of which an Ahmedabad-based one quoted the lowest amount for this first-of-its-kind project.

news.title: NBCC's net profit rises 64% to Rs 74 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: NBCC's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,960.91 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 37 per cent from Rs 1,426.27 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Akzo Nobel India's net profit dips 16% to Rs 55.72 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Akzo Nobel India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 743.90 crore in Q2 FY22, a growth of 21 per cent from Rs 612.60 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: After four years, SC nod for sand mining from river beds in Rajasthan
news.para: Sand mining from river beds has been allowed after almost four years and lease holders are expected to start operations over the next three months after getting environmental clearance (EC) from the ministry of environment, forest and climate change (MoEFCC).
